A Grandson of late Prime Minister, Sir Abubakar Tafawa Balewa, Alhaji Abubakar Billy Tafawa Balewa, has joined the race for Bauchi South senatorial seat to replace late Senator Ali Wakili. About 30 aspirants have so far joined the race for the Bauchi South senatorial seat, including a former Governor of the state, Malam Isa Yuguda. Billy, a consultant to the African Union (AU) and the Economic Community of West African States (ECOWAS), disclosed his intention in Bauchi while speaking to journalists. He said he wanted to run for the Bauchi South senate seat to follow the footsteps of his grandfather and other leaders in providing dividends of democracy not only to his immediate constituency but to Bauchi State and Nigeria at large. He commended late Sen. Wakili and the Speaker of the House of Representatives, Yakubu Dogara, for their determination and providing dividends of democracy to the people of their constituencies and Nigeria as a whole.ý ýBilly disclosed that he arrived at the decision to contest after wide consultation with stakeholders in all the seven local government areas of Bauchi South Senatorial District.